verses.text_plain: Hear ye the word which the Lord speaketh unto you, O house of Israel:
verses.verse_html: 1Hear ye the word which the Lord speaketh unto you, O house of Israel:

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord, Learn not the way of the heathen, and be not dismayed at the signs of heaven; for the heathen are dismayed at them.
verses.verse_html: 2Thus saith the Lord, Learn not the way of the heathen, and be not dismayed at the signs of heaven; for the heathen are dismayed at them.

verses.text_plain: For the customs of the people are vain: for one cutteth a tree out of the forest, the work of the hands of the workman, with the axe.
verses.verse_html:
3For the customs of the people are vain: for one cutteth a tree out of the forest, the work of the hands of the workman, with the axe. ▼
▼ customs…: Heb. statutes, or, ordinances are vanity

footnotes.body_text: ▼ customs…: Heb. statutes, or, ordinances are vanity
footnotes.body_html: ▼ customs…: Heb. statutes, or, ordinances are vanity

verses.text_plain: They deck it with silver and with gold; they fasten it with nails and with hammers, that it move not.
verses.verse_html: 4They deck it with silver and with gold; they fasten it with nails and with hammers, that it move not.

verses.text_plain: They are upright as the palm tree, but speak not: they must needs be borne, because they cannot go. Be not afraid of them; for they cannot do evil, neither also is it in them to do good.
verses.verse_html: 5They are upright as the palm tree, but speak not: they must needs be borne, because they cannot go. Be not afraid of them; for they cannot do evil, neither also is it in them to do good.

tokens.text: of them; for they cannot do evil

verses.text_plain: Forasmuch as there is none like unto thee, O Lord; thou art great, and thy name is great in might.
verses.verse_html: 6Forasmuch as there is none like unto thee, O Lord; thou art great, and thy name is great in might.

tokens.text: none like unto thee, O Lord

verses.text_plain: Who would not fear thee, O King of nations? for to thee doth it appertain: forasmuch as among all the wise men of the nations, and in all their kingdoms, there is none like unto thee.
verses.verse_html:
7Who would not fear thee, O King of nations? for to thee doth it appertain: forasmuch as among all the wise men of the nations, and in all their kingdoms, there is none like unto thee. ▼
▼ to…: or, it liketh thee

tokens.text: for to thee doth it appertain
forasmuch as among all the wise

footnotes.body_html: ▼ to…: or, it liketh thee

verses.text_plain: But they are altogether brutish and foolish: the stock is a doctrine of vanities.
verses.verse_html:
8But they are altogether brutish and foolish: the stock is a doctrine of vanities. ▼
▼ altogether: Heb. in one, or, at once

footnotes.body_text: ▼ altogether: Heb. in one, or, at once
footnotes.body_html: ▼ altogether: Heb. in one, or, at once

verses.text_plain: Silver spread into plates is brought from Tarshish, and gold from Uphaz, the work of the workman, and of the hands of the founder: blue and purple is their clothing: they are all the work of cunning men.
verses.verse_html: 9Silver spread into plates is brought from Tarshish, and gold from Uphaz, the work of the workman, and of the hands of the founder: blue and purple is their clothing: they are all the work of cunning men.

verses.text_plain: But the Lord is the true God, he is the living God, and an everlasting king: at his wrath the earth shall tremble, and the nations shall not be able to abide his indignation.
verses.verse_html:
10But the Lord is the true God, he is the living God, and an everlasting king: at his wrath the earth shall tremble, and the nations shall not be able to abide his indignation. ▼
▼ true…: Heb. God of truth
 , ▼
▼ living God: Heb. living Gods
 , ▼
▼ everlasting…: Heb. king of eternity

tokens.text: shall not be able to abide

footnotes.body_html: ▼ true…: Heb. God of truth
▼ living God: Heb. living Gods
▼ everlasting…: Heb. king of eternity

verses.text_plain: Thus shall ye say unto them, The gods that have not made the heavens and the earth, even they shall perish from the earth, and from under these heavens.
verses.verse_html: 11Thus shall ye say unto them, The gods that have not made the heavens and the earth, even they shall perish from the earth, and from under these heavens.

verses.text_plain: He hath made the earth by his power, he hath established the world by his wisdom, and hath stretched out the heavens by his discretion.
verses.verse_html: 12He hath made the earth by his power, he hath established the world by his wisdom, and hath stretched out the heavens by his discretion.

verses.text_plain: When he uttereth his voice, there is a multitude of waters in the heavens, and he causeth the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings with rain, and bringeth forth the wind out of his treasures.
verses.verse_html:
13When he uttereth his voice, there is a multitude of waters in the heavens, and he causeth the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings with rain, and bringeth forth the wind out of his treasures. ▼
▼ multitude: or, noise
 , ▼
▼ with: or, for

verses.text_plain: Every man is brutish in his knowledge: every founder is confounded by the graven image: for his molten image is falsehood, and there is no breath in them.
verses.verse_html:
14Every man is brutish in his knowledge: every founder is confounded by the graven image: for his molten image is falsehood, and there is no breath in them. ▼
▼ brutish in his knowledge: or, more brutish than to know

footnotes.body_text: ▼ brutish in his knowledge: or, more brutish than to know
footnotes.body_html: ▼ brutish in his knowledge: or, more brutish than to know

verses.text_plain: They are vanity, and the work of errors: in the time of their visitation they shall perish.
verses.verse_html: 15They are vanity, and the work of errors: in the time of their visitation they shall perish.

verses.text_plain: The portion of Jacob is not like them: for he is the former of all things; and Israel is the rod of his inheritance: The Lord of hosts is his name.
verses.verse_html: 16The portion of Jacob is not like them: for he is the former of all things; and Israel is the rod of his inheritance: The Lord of hosts is his name.

verses.text_plain: Gather up thy wares out of the land, O inhabitant of the fortress.
verses.verse_html:
17Gather up thy wares out of the land, O inhabitant of the fortress. ▼
▼ inhabitant: Heb. inhabitress

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will sling out the inhabitants of the land at this once, and will distress them, that they may find it so.
verses.verse_html: 18For thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will sling out the inhabitants of the land at this once, and will distress them, that they may find it so.

verses.text_plain: Woe is me for my hurt! my wound is grievous: but I said, Truly this is a grief, and I must bear it.
verses.verse_html: 19Woe is me for my hurt! my wound is grievous: but I said, Truly this is a grief, and I must bear it.

verses.text_plain: My tabernacle is spoiled, and all my cords are broken: my children are gone forth of me, and they are not: there is none to stretch forth my tent any more, and to set up my curtains.
verses.verse_html: 20My tabernacle is spoiled, and all my cords are broken: my children are gone forth of me, and they are not: there is none to stretch forth my tent any more, and to set up my curtains.

tokens.text: any more, and to set up

verses.text_plain: For the pastors are become brutish, and have not sought the Lord: therefore they shall not prosper, and all their flocks shall be scattered.
verses.verse_html: 21For the pastors are become brutish, and have not sought the Lord: therefore they shall not prosper, and all their flocks shall be scattered.

verses.text_plain: Behold, the noise of the bruit is come, and a great commotion out of the north country, to make the cities of Judah desolate, and a den of dragons.
verses.verse_html: 22Behold, the noise of the bruit is come, and a great commotion out of the north country, to make the cities of Judah desolate, and a den of dragons.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, I know that the way of man is not in himself: it is not in man that walketh to direct his steps.
verses.verse_html: 23O Lord, I know that the way of man is not in himself: it is not in man that walketh to direct his steps.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, correct me, but with judgment; not in thine anger, lest thou bring me to nothing.
verses.verse_html:
24O Lord, correct me, but with judgment; not in thine anger, lest thou bring me to nothing. ▼
▼ bring…: Heb. diminish me

tokens.text: lest thou bring me to nothing

footnotes.body_html: ▼ bring…: Heb. diminish me

verses.text_plain: Pour out thy fury upon the heathen that know thee not, and upon the families that call not on thy name: for they have eaten up Jacob, and devoured him, and consumed him, and have made his habitation desolate.
verses.verse_html: 25Pour out thy fury upon the heathen that know thee not, and upon the families that call not on thy name: for they have eaten up Jacob, and devoured him, and consumed him, and have made his habitation desolate.

tokens.text: thee not, and upon the families
him, and have made his habitation
